# Illustrative per-layer RC for a sky130-class metal stack (not signoff values).
# layer  res(ohm/um)  cap(fF/um)  coupling(fF/um)  s_ref(um)
#   coupling is the lateral coupling per micron of parallel run, at spacing s_ref;
#   it falls off ~1/gap and is ignored beyond couple_cutoff. s_ref is optional.
li1      12.8         0.060       0.030            0.17
met1      0.125       0.078       0.050            0.14
met2      0.125       0.072       0.044            0.14
met3      0.047       0.068       0.040            0.30
via       9.3
couple_cutoff 2.0     # um — ignore lateral coupling between wires farther apart than this
# inter-layer (crossover) areal coupling, fF/um^2 (needs LEF widths):
interlayer li1  met1  0.030
interlayer met1 met2  0.035
interlayer met2 met3  0.032
